### VS Code ###
# Ignore machine-specific VS Code state, but COMMIT the generic run configs (launch.json / tasks.json)
# so contributors get working Run/Debug + the prepare-args preLaunchTask out of the box.
.vscode/*
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/tasks.json

### Mac OS ###
.DS_Store

### Minecraft Modding ###
run/*
# Track the gallery screenshots (the capture harness writes here) so CI/listing automation can pick
# them up. Everything else under run/ stays ignored. (Git needs each parent dir re-included.)
!run/screenshots/
run/screenshots/*
!run/screenshots/nerospace/
!**/src/**/run/
**/src/generated/**/.cache/
repo/
!**/src/**/repo/
PROJECT_PLAN.md
/tools/__pycache__
runs/
# …but DO track the capture-harness gallery screenshots under the NeoForge 26.2 client run, so the
# Sync-Modrinth-gallery workflow can pick them up. Re-include each parent dir before the files — git
# will not descend into an excluded directory, so the `**` alone is not enough.
# Whitelist recipe (git docs): at each level un-ignore the dir so git descends, then re-ignore that
# dir's OTHER contents with `/*`, so ONLY the screenshots/nerospace/ leaf ends up tracked — every
# other run artifact (logs, options, saves, caches, the rest of client/ and runs/) stays ignored.
!neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/
neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/*
!neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/client/
neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/client/*
!neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/client/screenshots/
neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/client/screenshots/*
!neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/client/screenshots/nerospace/
!neoforge/versions/26.2/runs/client/screenshots/nerospace/**
/fabric/runs
/.github/scripts/__pycache__
/tools/gradle-mcp/node_modules
